    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@vvo Yes, yes I do\n\nMy typical situation is that I have a central index that contains items for several countries. Then users access www.mywebsite.com/us or www.mywebsite.com/uk and search for items within that country\n\nRight now I'm working around it with a hack by adding a default widget with disjunctive facet point to the current country (but that get reset with a clearAll widget)\n\nI tried to use facetFilters in searchParameters, and it does pass that up to Algolia for the initial search, however, subsequent search got messed up and never run correctly.\n",
