  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Right now I'm working around it with a hack by adding a default widget with disjunctive facet point to the current country (but that get reset with a clearAll widget)\n\nThat's the way to do it, unfortunately for now the \"clear all\" widget is not able to avoid clearing some filters.\n\nWe will make this easier in the long term.\n\nFor now, what you can do is use the currentRefinedValues with the clearAll option along with onlyListedAttributes:\n\n``` js\nvar clearAll = instantsearch.widgets.currentRefinedValues({\n    container: \"#active-refinements\",\n    clearAll: 'after',\n    attributes: [{\n      name: 'attr' // you must put a list of attributes you want the clearAll button to clear\n    }],\n    onlyListedAttributes: true\n  })\n);\n```\n\nWhen clicking clearAll of this widget, it should clear the list of attributes you gave but not the language.\n",
    "created_at": "2016-06-10T09:37:56Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1058#issuecomment-225138897",
    "id": 225138897,
